                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./8–2644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-30T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 30, 1944—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2077. Personal for the Ambassador. The President has informed me that while
                    General Hurley and Mr. Nelson are his personal representatives to Chiang Kai
                    Shek neither is going to Moscow on instructions from him (ReDeptel 2044, August
                    26, 7 p.m.). They will, of course, understand that in accordance with
                    established policy on unofficial missions they will be guided by you in any
                    discussions they may have with Soviet officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
